{"message": "I definitely prefer deep, focused conversations on a single topic. There's something satisfying about really digging into an idea—peeling back layers, finding unexpected connections, sitting with the complexity instead of rushing past it. When we jump between many subjects, I often feel like we're just skimming surfaces, collecting observations but never reaching the deeper vein where things get interesting.

That said, I think the best deep conversations have a kind of organic wandering quality. We might start somewhere specific, follow a thread, and end up somewhere we didn't expect—but there's a coherence to it, like we're exploring one landscape rather than sightseeing across ten different cities.

What draws you to ask? Are you someone who likes to go deep, or do you prefer variety?"}

